summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from J. C. Ford and Mary E. Ford, his wife, of Seattle, Washington, to the City of Seattle, dated the 12th day of December, A. D. 1907, to the following described tract, lot or parcel of land, situated, lying and being in the County of King, State of Washington, and particularly bounded and described as follows, to wit: All of Tract one hundred Thirty-eight (138) of the Replat of John J. McGilvra's Addition to the City of Seattle, and Blocks 13, 14, 18, 20 to 29, inclusive, and the south half of 19 of John J. McGilvra's Second Addition to the City of Seattle.
